      <i>Developers can now create Alexa experiences for customers in
      Japan‚ÄîAlexa Skills Kit also now available in <location value="LC/jp;LB/eas" idsrc="xmltag.org">Japan</location>, and Alexa Voice
      Service coming later this month</i>
    </p>
<p>    <location value="LU/us.wa.seatle" idsrc="xmltag.org">SEATTLE</location>--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Nov. 8, 2017--
      (NASDAQ: AMZN)‚ÄîAmazon today announced that Alexa and Echo are now
      available by invitation in <location value="LC/jp;LB/eas" idsrc="xmltag.org">Japan</location>. Additionally, developers can now use
      the Alexa Skills Kit to create Japanese Alexa experiences, and will soon
      be able to use the Alexa Voice Service to integrate Alexa into products
      for Japanese customers. Read the press release announcing Alexa in
      <location value="LC/jp;LB/eas" idsrc="xmltag.org">Japan</location>: <a href="http://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Famazon-press.jp&amp;esheet=51713020&amp;newsitemid=20171107006944&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=https%3A%2F%2Famazon-press.jp&amp;index=1&amp;md5=cc238297745a22a43e4383e8bd301e46" rel="nofollow">https://amazon-press.jp</a>.
    </p>
<p>
      ‚ÄúTens of millions of customers already love Alexa and we‚Äôre thrilled to
